\end_inset

cut out the middlemen
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 This is because traders,
 both small and large,
 also engage to some extent in arbitrage to capitalize on price seasonality,
 buying up maize grain from farmers immediately post harvest when prices are low and selling during the lean season when maize is scarce and prices are high 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "van2015inter,burke2019sell"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
