\begin_layout Standard
Uganda’s maize flour retail sector is shaped by strong demand,
 price sensitivity,
 and evolving consumer preferences.
 As a staple food,
 maize flour is consumed widely across all income levels,
 with demand driven by population growth,
 urbanization,
 and food security needs 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
